# Claims Rules for AICostPlanner

## Absolute Bans

Never write these words/phrases:

### Price Claims
- cheapest
- lowest price
- most affordable
- best value
- lowest cost
- rock-bottom

### Guarantee Claims
- guaranteed
- guaranteed compatible
- guaranteed to work
- always available
- always works
- 100% compatible

### Availability Claims
- all models available
- every model supported
- complete model list
- unlimited models

### Usage Claims
- unlimited usage
- unlimited API calls
- unlimited requests
- no rate limits

### Billing Claims
- no billing risk
- no surprise charges
- no hidden fees
- transparent pricing (without qualification)

### Partnership Claims
- official partner
- official reseller
- certified partner
- authorized dealer

### Provider Endorsements
- RutaAPI supports [unspecified model]
- RutaAPI supports every model
- RutaAPI is the cheapest
- RutaAPI is the best

### Exact Pricing
- exact pricing: $X.XX
- costs exactly $X
- "You will pay $X"

## Safe Alternatives

### Instead of Price Claims
- "Check live pricing"
- "Pricing varies by model"
- "Compare provider pricing"
- "Prices can change"

### Instead of Guarantee Claims
- "Most models are compatible"
- "Check model availability"
- "Test with your workflow"

### Instead of Availability Claims
- "Many popular models available"
- "Check provider documentation"
- "Model availability varies"

### Instead of Billing Claims
- "Monitor your usage"
- "Set usage alerts"
- "Review provider billing"
- "Test small to understand costs"

### For Provider Info
- "Check official provider docs"
- "Verify with provider"
- "Pricing from provider documentation"

## Verification Required

Only state specific prices or features if:
1. Verified from official provider documentation
2. Verified from live provider website
3. Stated as "as of [date]" with source

## Media API Specific

For video/image generation:
- NEVER claim RutaAPI supports Sora, Kling, Runway without verification
- Use "examples of pricing patterns"
- Include "model availability can change"
- Include Sora deprecation/availability warning

## Testing Requirements

After writing any content:
1. Run `npm run validate:claims`
2. Fix any flagged claims
3. Verify no banned words present
4. Check for safe alternatives

